@Joey
    I made the same observation, how sonic BOOMS get louder as they get closer to the ground. It makes me wonder if there is a way for planes to take off higher, or to minimize the loud sound. 
    BOOM! BOOM! BOOM!!!!

@Elvis
    The leading edge boom being louder could be due to the shape and speed at that point in flight, producing stronger shock waves.

    It also highlights the impact on community. The SONIC BOOMS can definitely harm people in the area, especially the elderly population. This raises important questions about how we balance technological progress with public health.
